      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">6th April [187]1. ¶ editorial addition. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor by direction of the above Committee to acknowledge your letter of the 10th March addressed to His Honor Sir Redmond Barry ¶ M to R. ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.04.06b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Marcus Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter no. 62/I.T.M.71, Outward letterbook 1870-9 pp. 167-169, Industrial and Technological Museum and Public Library, Museum Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">6th April [187]1.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor by direction of the above Committee to acknowledge your letter of the 10th March addressed to His Honor Sir Redmond Barry<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to R. Barry, 10 March 1871.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and to inform you in reply that the Committee much regret that you should have misunderstood the tenor of their communications with you</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Committee instruct me to assure you that they have the highest possible respect for your scientific attainments and social and official position, and that they would on no account have you imagine that they would act towards you in any manner that was not consonant with that opinion and the greatest consideration for yourself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>But the Committee desire me to point out to you that they have already expended on the Phytologic Section a larger sum than that expended on other departments of the Museum, and that it is their duty as Trustees of the Institution to exercise in their disbursements a most strict economy</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Committee think moreover that you have omitted to consider the fact that they — so far from refusing the needful funds to enable you to carry on your valuable labours in connection with the Museum — have begged you to name the sum required to fully complete the Phytologic section in order that they might give to the question of further expenditure their best consideration The Committee again desire me to ask you to name the sum you need.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With reference to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">index plantarum</hi>
               </seg>, the Committee regret that owing to arrangements made with the Printer, and the fact that they have already been compelled to refuse to print addenda to other lectures — in the shape of notes and diagrams, they cannot publish your most valuable and interesting list together with the volume of lectures,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Industrial and Technological Museum (Melbourne) (1871).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but unwilling that the public should be deprived of the benefit of your labours and that you yourself should suffer the mortification of seeing your trouble and time expended to no purpose the Committee will publish a limited number of copies of your lecture<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">separately</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with the index attached<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to R. Berry 29 March 1871 he asked<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>again<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>whether the Industrial Commission would publish the appendix planned to accompany B71.03.10.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The proposed appendix was instead published as B71.06.02, with a comment in the introduction that it was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">originally prepared and alluded to as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">an<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">appendage to a lecture</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">recently delivered at the Melbourne Industrial</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Museum</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">'.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Again assuring you of the consideration of the Committee</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marcus Clarke</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. Von Müller C.M.G. M.D. Ph.D. F.R.S<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Director of the Botanic Gardens</p>
         </div>
